Detailed Description

cvmx_mio_fus_prog

DON'T PUT IN HRM*

Notes: This CSR is not present in the HRM.

To write a bank of fuses, SW must set MIO_FUS_WADR[ADDR] to the bank to be programmed and then set each bit within MIO_FUS_BNK_DATX to indicate which fuses to blow. Once ADDR, and DAT are setup, SW can write to MIO_FUS_PROG[PROG] to start the bank write and poll on PROG. Once PROG is clear, the bank write is complete.

A soft blow is still subject to lockdown fuses. After a soft/warm reset, the chip will behave as though the fuses were actually blown. A cold reset restores the actual fuse valuse.
